defaultAbout The Royal College of Pathologistsdefault&#xa0;default1.1
default              
defaultThe Royal College of Pathologists (RCPath) is a professional membership organisation with charitable status. It is committed to setting and maintaining professional standards and to promoting excellence in the teaching and practice of pathology. 
defaultPathology 
defaultis the science at the heart of modern medicine and is 
defaulta core component in 70
default%
default of clinical interventions (di
defaultagnosis, 
defaultchoice of treatment, efficacy of treatment)
default. The College aims to advance the science and practice of pathology, to provide public education,
default to promote research in pathology and to disseminate the results. We have members across 19 
defaultspecialties 
defaultworking in hospital laboratories, universities and industry worldwide to diagnose, treat and prevent illness.
