defaultInappropriate over-testing has significant effects on financial expenditure, not only on the direct cost to the laboratory, but also as a result of the costs of subsequent 
defaultunnecessary, knock-
defaulton investigations that may be ordered following the inevitable fa
defaultlse positive result. The damage to patient care may
