default5.default              defaultPathology Demand Optimisation (PDO)default&#xa0;
default5.1
default              
defaultIn 2013, the RCPath set
default up a Pathology Demand Optimisation (PDO) Group comprised of representatives from the major pathology disciplines, pathology societies, industry representatives, the National Pathology Programme and lay involvement. The purpose of this initiative was to al
defaultlow the major pathology stakeholders to work with already established leaders in the field of Laboratory Demand Management research to enable the development of specific Pathology Demand Management Guidance in the form of a toolkit of recommendations and a
default Minimum Retesting Interval (MRI) advisory strategy. 
default&#xa0;
default5.2
default              
defaultThe 
defaultuse of 
defaultMRIs is
default of vital importance and aim
defaults
default to define the minimum time interval whereby tests should be repeated
default. This avoids
default unnecessary repeat testing – a common problem in secondary care with laboratory tests frequently being repeated whenever the patient crosses an interface of care
default,
default such as a ward transfer. This is of increasing importance following commissioning and the in
defaultherent risk of multiple pathology providers. While developments with the N
defaulta
defaultt
defaultional Laboratory Medicine Catalogue
default (NLMC)
default, which should improve communication and transferability of pathology 
defaultresults, will help, the availability of consensus, peer reviewed or 
defaultin some cases evidence based MRIs are essential.
default&#xa0;
